productivity.title: Nonfarm Business Output Per Hour (quarterly, productivity)

fred_labor_squeeze.interpretation: If unit labor costs rising while productivity flat/falling, industries are in a squeeze. Cross-reference with BLS occupation data to find which specific roles are driving costs.

fred_credit_stress.interpretation: Rising delinquency + widening HY spread = businesses under financial stress. These are the ones most vulnerable to cost-structure disruption from agentic competitors.

fred_job_gaps.interpretation: High openings + high quits + low unemployment = tight labor market where employers cannot fill roles. These gaps are where agentic substitution faces least resistance.

fred_rates.interpretation: High rates favor cash-flow-positive, low-burn businesses. This aligns with agentic-first cost structures. Inverted yield curve = recession signal = accelerated liquidation cascades.

CPATAX.title: Corporate Profits After Tax with IVA and CCAdj (quarterly)

fred_profitability.interpretation: Declining corporate profits = margin compression. Divergence between financial and nonfinancial profits indicates sector-specific stress patterns.

STLFSI4.title: St. Louis Fed Financial Stress Index (weekly)

DRTSCILM.title: Net % Banks Tightening C&I Loan Standards, Large Firms (quarterly)

DRTSCLCC.title: Net % Banks Tightening Credit Card Loan Standards (quarterly)

fred_stress.interpretation: Rising VIX + tightening lending standards = credit stress. Banks tightening C&I loans = incumbents losing access to restructuring capital. Favors cash-flow-positive agentic entrants.

ECIWAG.title: ECI Wages and Salaries All Civilian (quarterly)

fred_sector_costs.interpretation: Sectors where total compensation grows fastest offer widest cost advantage for agentic substitution. Compare Professional & Business Services vs. Education & Health to find divergence.

fred_small_biz.interpretation: Rising business applications + rising delinquency = churn. Old businesses dying, new ones forming. Applications without planned wages may indicate solo/agentic business formation.

fred_assets.interpretation: Rising liabilities + falling capex = businesses taking on debt without investing. Inventory buildup may signal demand collapse. These are pre-liquidation indicators.

bls_industry.interpretation: Industries with flat/declining employment but rising wages are in a labor squeeze. Cross-reference with FRED unit labor costs to confirm cascade pressure.

bls_wages.interpretation: Rising wages = growing cost advantage for agentic businesses. Each percentage point of wage inflation widens the moat for AI-first cost structures that have near-zero marginal labor cost.

bls_jolts.interpretation: High openings + high quits = structural labor shortage. Industries where this persists for 12+ months have a gap that agentic substitution can fill with regulatory tailwind (solving a shortage, not displacing workers).

bls_occupational.interpretation: Occupations with high wages and large employment bases represent the biggest addressable markets for agentic disruption. Rising wages widen the cost advantage each year. Declining employment may indicate disruption already underway.

CES6054000003.title: Avg Hourly Earnings, Professional and Technical Services

CES6500000003.title: Avg Hourly Earnings, Education and Health Services

bls_wage_premium.interpretation: Industries with highest and fastest-rising hourly earnings represent the largest cost-advantage opportunity for agentic businesses. Compare growth rates to prioritize where P3 moat widens fastest.

edgar_distress.interpretation: Companies filing 8-Ks about restructuring, 10-Ks with going concern warnings, or mentioning AI as a risk factor are potential targets. Their customers and contracts may become available as they consolidate or exit.

data.query: "artificial intelligence" AND ("implementation challenges" OR "transition" OR "digital transformation")

edgar_ai_failures.interpretation: Companies discussing AI implementation challenges in 10-K filings are signaling low mobility. They recognize the need to adopt AI but face organizational barriers. Their market position is vulnerable to agentic-first entrants.
